    {
      "id": "working_length_and_apex_locators",
      "title": "Optimizing Working Length Determination with Modern Apex Locators",
      "slug": "optimizing-working-length-apex-locators",
      "summary": "How to integrate electronic apex locators into your daily workflow for more predictable working length control.",
      "body": "Accurate working length determination is foundational to endodontic success. Modern electronic apex locators have significantly improved precision compared with radiographic methods alone.\n\nThis article reviews best practices for using apex locators, including isolation, canal pre-flaring, and managing challenging scenarios such as open apices or metallic restorations. It also covers how to interpret apex locator display readings and combine them with radiographic confirmation.\n\nWe compare entry-level and premium devices, highlighting clinical situations where advanced features such as multi-frequency measurement, large color displays, and integrated motors can enhance efficiency and safety.",
      "tags": [
        "working_length",
        "apex_locator",
        "electronic_devices",
        "clinical_technique"
